title: High school football: Late score lifts Willowbrook against Morton
text:
High school football: Late score lifts Willowbrook against Morton Published: Monday, Oct. 5, 2015 9:07 a.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
BERWYN â€“ Sophomore Jack Jessen's 1-yard touchdown run with just 20.9 seconds left finished a wild back-and-forth second half battle as Willowbrook fought off host Morton 38-31 on Oct. 2. 
Jessen rushed for 32 of the 53 yards on the deciding drive. Morton had tied the game at 31 with 6:29 to go on Antonio Tamayo's 11-yard TD pass to Tavolis Parker. 
Sophomore Greg Hoard scored the Mustangs' first three touchdowns of the night, including an 80-yard screen pass and run from Tamayo that began Morton's third-quarter rally from a 24-13 deficit. 
Willowbrook quarterback Billy Degnan threw for 180 yards and three touchdowns on the night, two to Ronnie Reitz. 
The Warriors led 14-13 at halftime.
